# Kubernetes PoC on Proxmox VE — 3 Control Plane / 5 Worker

Provisioning with Terraform (`bpg/proxmox`), bootstrapping with `kubeadm` via Ansible.
Target: a throwaway-but-realistic HA cluster for testing workloads, upgrades, and failure scenarios.

---

## 1. Architecture

```
                    ┌──────────────────────┐
                    │  VIP 10.10.10.100    │  ← kube-vip (ARP mode)
                    │  :6443 control plane │
                    └──────────┬───────────┘
                               │
        ┌──────────────┬───────┴───────┬──────────────┐
        │              │               │              │
   ┌────▼────┐    ┌────▼────┐    ┌────▼────┐
   │ cp-01   │    │ cp-02   │    │ cp-03   │     etcd stacked (quorum = 2)
   │ .11     │    │ .12     │    │ .13     │
   └─────────┘    └─────────┘    └─────────┘

   ┌─────────┐ ┌─────────┐ ┌─────────┐ ┌─────────┐ ┌─────────┐
   │ wk-01   │ │ wk-02   │ │ wk-03   │ │ wk-04   │ │ wk-05   │
   │ .21     │ │ .22     │ │ .23     │ │ .24     │ │ .25     │
   └─────────┘ └─────────┘ └─────────┘ └─────────┘ └─────────┘
```

| Component | Choice | Why |
|---|---|---|
| Provider | `bpg/proxmox` | Actively maintained; `Telmate/proxmox` is effectively abandoned |
| Guest OS | Ubuntu 24.04 LTS cloud image | cloud-init native, well-tested with kubeadm |
| Runtime | containerd 1.7+ | dockershim is long gone |
| Bootstrap | kubeadm + Ansible | Terraform makes VMs, Ansible makes a cluster — don't mix them |
| CP VIP | kube-vip (static pod, ARP) | No extra VMs vs. HAProxy+keepalived pair |
| CNI | Cilium | eBPF, kube-proxy replacement optional, good observability for a PoC |
| LB | MetalLB (L2) | Gives `type: LoadBalancer` on bare Proxmox |
| Storage | local-path (default) + optional NFS CSI | Keeps PoC simple |

