## 2. Requirements

### 2.1 Proxmox host sizing

| Role | Count | vCPU | RAM | Disk |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| Control plane | 3 | 2 | 4 GB | 40 GB |
| Worker | 5 | 4 | 8 GB | 60 GB |
| **Total (guests)** | **8** | **26** | **52 GB** | **420 GB** |

Host minimum: **16 physical cores / 64 GB RAM / 500 GB SSD or NVMe**.
Spinning rust will make etcd unhappy — `etcd_disk_wal_fsync_duration_seconds` will spike and you'll get spurious leader elections. Use SSD/NVMe for the VM storage pool.

CPU overcommit at 26 vCPU on 16 cores is fine for a PoC. RAM is **not** overcommittable here — don't rely on ballooning for etcd nodes.

### 2.2 Software

| Tool | Version |
|---|---|
| Proxmox VE | 8.2+ |
| Terraform | 1.9+ (or OpenTofu 1.8+) |
| Ansible | 2.16+ |
| kubectl / kubeadm / kubelet | 1.31.x |
| Helm | 3.15+ |

### 2.3 Network plan

| Item | Value |
|---|---|
| VM subnet | `10.10.10.0/24` (vmbr0) |
| Gateway | `10.10.10.1` |
| Control plane VIP | `10.10.10.100` |
| CP nodes | `10.10.10.11-13` |
| Workers | `10.10.10.21-25` |
| MetalLB pool | `10.10.10.200-10.10.10.240` |
| Pod CIDR | `10.244.0.0/16` |
| Service CIDR | `10.96.0.0/12` |

The VIP and MetalLB pool must be **outside** your DHCP scope. Pod/Service CIDRs must not overlap the VM subnet.

### 2.4 Prerequisites checklist

- [ ] Proxmox node reachable, `pveversion` ≥ 8.2
- [ ] Storage pool for VM disks (`local-lvm` / `local-zfs`) with 500 GB free
- [ ] Storage pool that accepts `snippets` and `import` content types (usually `local`)
- [ ] Bridge `vmbr0` on the VM VLAN
- [ ] API token created (see below)
- [ ] SSH keypair for the `ubuntu` user
- [ ] Nested virtualisation **not** required, but `cpu type = host` is

