## 3. Proxmox prep

### 3.1 API token

```bash
# On the Proxmox host
pveum user add terraform@pve
pveum role add TerraformRole -privs \
  "Datastore.Allocate Datastore.AllocateSpace Datastore.Audit \
   Pool.Allocate Sys.Audit Sys.Console Sys.Modify \
   VM.Allocate VM.Audit VM.Clone VM.Config.CDROM VM.Config.Cloudinit \
   VM.Config.CPU VM.Config.Disk VM.Config.HWType VM.Config.Memory \
   VM.Config.Network VM.Config.Options VM.Migrate VM.Monitor \
   VM.PowerMgmt SDN.Use"
pveum aclmod / -user terraform@pve -role TerraformRole
pveum user token add terraform@pve tfprovider --privsep=0
```

Copy the token value — it's shown once.

### 3.2 Enable snippets on `local`

```bash
pvesm set local --content backup,iso,vztmpl,snippets,import
```

### 3.3 Allow the provider to SSH (needed for cloud-image import)

`bpg/proxmox` shells into the node for some operations. Either use `root@pam` for the SSH block or:

```bash
useradd -m -s /bin/bash terraform
usermod -aG sudo terraform
echo "terraform ALL=(root) NOPASSWD: /sbin/pvesm, /usr/bin/qm, /sbin/qmrestore" \
  > /etc/sudoers.d/terraform
mkdir -p /home/terraform/.ssh && chmod 700 /home/terraform/.ssh
# paste your pubkey into /home/terraform/.ssh/authorized_keys
```

