## 6. Bootstrap with Ansible

### 6.1 Common prep (all nodes)

`ansible/roles/common/tasks/main.yml` essentials:

```yaml
- name: Disable swap
  ansible.builtin.command: swapoff -a
  changed_when: false

- name: Load kernel modules
  ansible.builtin.copy:
    dest: /etc/modules-load.d/k8s.conf
    content: |
      overlay
      br_netfilter

- name: Sysctl for k8s
  ansible.builtin.copy:
    dest: /etc/sysctl.d/99-k8s.conf
    content: |
      net.bridge.bridge-nf-call-iptables  = 1
      net.bridge.bridge-nf-call-ip6tables = 1
      net.ipv4.ip_forward                 = 1
  notify: reload sysctl

- name: /etc/hosts entries
  ansible.builtin.lineinfile:
    path: /etc/hosts
    line: "{{ hostvars[item].ansible_host }} {{ item }}"
  loop: "{{ groups['k8s'] }}"
```

### 6.2 containerd

```yaml
- name: Install containerd
  ansible.builtin.apt:
    name: containerd
    state: present
    update_cache: true

- name: Default config
  ansible.builtin.shell: containerd config default > /etc/containerd/config.toml
  args: { creates: /etc/containerd/config.toml }

- name: Use systemd cgroup driver
  ansible.builtin.replace:
    path: /etc/containerd/config.toml
    regexp: 'SystemdCgroup = false'
    replace: 'SystemdCgroup = true'
  notify: restart containerd
```

> `SystemdCgroup = true` is the single most common cause of a kubelet that flaps and never goes Ready. Don't skip it.

### 6.3 kubeadm packages

```yaml
- name: Kubernetes apt key
  ansible.builtin.get_url:
    url: https://pkgs.k8s.io/core:/stable:/v1.31/deb/Release.key
    dest: /tmp/k8s.key

- name: Dearmor key
  ansible.builtin.shell: gpg --dearmor -o /etc/apt/keyrings/kubernetes.gpg /tmp/k8s.key
  args: { creates: /etc/apt/keyrings/kubernetes.gpg }

- name: Repo
  ansible.builtin.apt_repository:
    repo: "deb [signed-by=/etc/apt/keyrings/kubernetes.gpg] https://pkgs.k8s.io/core:/stable:/v1.31/deb/ /"
    filename: kubernetes

- name: Install kube packages
  ansible.builtin.apt:
    name: [kubelet=1.31.*, kubeadm=1.31.*, kubectl=1.31.*]
    state: present
    update_cache: true

- name: Pin versions
  ansible.builtin.dpkg_selections:
    name: "{{ item }}"
    selection: hold
  loop: [kubelet, kubeadm, kubectl]
```

### 6.4 kube-vip static pod (control plane nodes, before init)

```bash
# Run on each CP node — generates /etc/kubernetes/manifests/kube-vip.yaml
export VIP=10.10.10.100
export INTERFACE=$(ip -4 route show default | awk '{print $5}')
export KVVERSION=v0.8.7

ctr image pull ghcr.io/kube-vip/kube-vip:$KVVERSION
ctr run --rm --net-host ghcr.io/kube-vip/kube-vip:$KVVERSION vip \
  /kube-vip manifest pod \
  --interface $INTERFACE \
  --address $VIP \
  --controlplane \
  --arp \
  --leaderElection \
  | tee /etc/kubernetes/manifests/kube-vip.yaml
```

On the **first** CP node only, add `super-admin.conf` handling for kube-vip ≥ 0.8:

```bash
sed -i 's#path: /etc/kubernetes/admin.conf#path: /etc/kubernetes/super-admin.conf#' \
  /etc/kubernetes/manifests/kube-vip.yaml
```

Revert it to `admin.conf` after all three CPs have joined.

### 6.5 Init the first control plane

`kubeadm-config.yaml`:

```yaml
apiVersion: kubeadm.k8s.io/v1beta4
kind: ClusterConfiguration
kubernetesVersion: v1.31.4
controlPlaneEndpoint: "10.10.10.100:6443"
networking:
  podSubnet: "10.244.0.0/16"
  serviceSubnet: "10.96.0.0/12"
apiServer:
  certSANs:
    - "10.10.10.100"
    - "10.10.10.11"
    - "10.10.10.12"
    - "10.10.10.13"
    - "k8s-api.lab.local"
---
apiVersion: kubelet.config.k8s.io/v1beta1
kind: KubeletConfiguration
cgroupDriver: systemd
```

```bash
sudo kubeadm init --config kubeadm-config.yaml --upload-certs
```

Save the two join commands it prints. Then:

```bash
mkdir -p $HOME/.kube
sudo cp -i /etc/kubernetes/admin.conf $HOME/.kube/config
sudo chown $(id -u):$(id -g) $HOME/.kube/config
kubectl get nodes    # NotReady until CNI is installed — expected
```

### 6.6 Join the other two control planes

```bash
sudo kubeadm join 10.10.10.100:6443 \
  --token <token> \
  --discovery-token-ca-cert-hash sha256:<hash> \
  --control-plane --certificate-key <cert-key>
```

Certificate key expires after 2 hours. Regenerate:

```bash
sudo kubeadm init phase upload-certs --upload-certs
sudo kubeadm token create --print-join-command
```

### 6.7 Join the 5 workers

```bash
sudo kubeadm join 10.10.10.100:6443 \
  --token <token> \
  --discovery-token-ca-cert-hash sha256:<hash>
```

Ansible-friendly version:

```yaml
- name: Generate join command
  ansible.builtin.command: kubeadm token create --print-join-command
  register: join_cmd
  delegate_to: "{{ groups['control_plane'][0] }}"
  run_once: true

- name: Join workers
  ansible.builtin.command: "{{ join_cmd.stdout }}"
  args: { creates: /etc/kubernetes/kubelet.conf }
```

