## 8. Validation

```bash
# Topology
kubectl get nodes -o wide
kubectl get pods -A
kubectl top nodes

# etcd health
kubectl -n kube-system exec -it etcd-k8s-cp-01 -- etcdctl \
  --endpoints=https://127.0.0.1:2379 \
  --cacert=/etc/kubernetes/pki/etcd/ca.crt \
  --cert=/etc/kubernetes/pki/etcd/server.crt \
  --key=/etc/kubernetes/pki/etcd/server.key \
  endpoint status --write-out=table

# Smoke test a LoadBalancer service
kubectl create deploy web --image=nginx --replicas=5
kubectl expose deploy web --port=80 --type=LoadBalancer
kubectl get svc web -w
curl http://<assigned-ip>

# Label the workers properly
for i in 1 2 3 4 5; do
  kubectl label node k8s-wk-0$i node-role.kubernetes.io/worker=""
done
```

### HA failure drills (the actual point of a PoC)

```bash
# 1. Kill a control plane — API should stay up via VIP failover
qm stop 9011
kubectl get nodes            # should still respond within ~5s

# 2. Kill a second — quorum lost, API goes read-only/down. Expected.
qm stop 9012
qm start 9011 9012

# 3. Drain a worker
kubectl drain k8s-wk-03 --ignore-daemonsets --delete-emptydir-data
kubectl uncordon k8s-wk-03
```

