## 9. Troubleshooting

| Symptom | Cause | Fix |
|---|---|---|
| Nodes stuck `NotReady` | No CNI installed | Install Cilium |
| kubelet crashlooping, `failed to run Kubelet` | swap still on, or cgroup driver mismatch | `swapoff -a`; set `SystemdCgroup = true` |
| `kubeadm join` times out on VIP | kube-vip static pod not running on CP-01 | `crictl ps -a \| grep vip`; check `/etc/kubernetes/manifests/kube-vip.yaml` |
| VIP unreachable | ARP mode blocked by switch/firewall | Test with `arping 10.10.10.100`; switch to BGP mode if needed |
| Terraform: `cloud-init drive not found` | `snippets` not enabled on datastore | `pvesm set local --content ...,snippets` |
| Terraform hangs on `agent enabled` | qemu-guest-agent not installed in image | Confirm vendor cloud-config ran: `cloud-init status --long` |
| MetalLB assigns IP, no traffic | Pool overlaps DHCP or another host | Pick a truly unused range |
| etcd `apply entries took too long` | Slow disk | Move VM storage to NVMe |

Useful one-liners:

```bash
journalctl -u kubelet -f --no-pager
crictl ps -a
crictl logs <container-id>
kubeadm certs check-expiration
cloud-init status --long && sudo cat /var/log/cloud-init-output.log
```

