## 11. Known limitations of this PoC

- **Single Proxmox host = single point of failure.** The 3-master HA is simulated; a host reboot takes the whole cluster. For a real HA test you need 3 Proxmox nodes with anti-affinity (HA groups).
- No backup of etcd. Add `etcdctl snapshot save` on a cron before you trust it with anything.
- Self-signed certs and `insecure = true` throughout.
- `kubeadm` join tokens are short-lived; automate regeneration if you re-run Ansible later.
- No secrets management — the API token lives in env vars. Move to Vault/SOPS before this pattern goes anywhere near prod.

